{"id":"https://contentapi.theodi.org/crime-and-justice-series.json","web_url":"http://theodi.org/crime-and-justice-series","slug":"crime-and-justice-series","title":"Crime and Justice: Open Data Challenge Series","format":"article","updated_at":"2015-09-11T09:54:04+00:00","created_at":"2013-03-27T15:49:15+00:00","tag_ids":["page"],"tags":[{"id":"https://contentapi.theodi.org/tags/articles/page.json","web_url":null,"title":"Page","details":{"description":"Page","type":"article"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://contentapi.theodi.org/with_tag.json?article=page","web_url":"http://theodi.org/tags/page","slug":"page"}}],"details":{"need_id":"","business_proposition":false,"description":"","excerpt":"<img src=\"http://bd7a65e2cb448908f934-86a50c88e47af9e1fb58ce0672b5a500.r32.cf3.rackcdn.com/uploads/assets/b3/16/52b3162ff362be6c87000012/image1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img pull-right\" id=\"52b3162f1f986a6d7b0000e7\">\r","language":"en","need_extended_font":false,"alternative_title":"","url":"","content":"<p><img src=\"http://bd7a65e2cb448908f934-86a50c88e47af9e1fb58ce0672b5a500.r32.cf3.rackcdn.com/uploads/assets/b3/16/52b3162ff362be6c87000012/image_1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img pull-right\" id=\"52b3162f1f986a6d7b0000e7\">\n<strong><em>The Crime and Justice Open Data Challenge is in its final stages.</em></strong> </p>\n<p>Three finalists, <strong>Total Car Check</strong>, <strong>Deaf Justice</strong> and <strong>Check That Bike</strong> were chosen at the Creation and Innovation Weekend in September 2013, read about the <a href=\"http://storify.com/siwhitehouse/open-data-challenge-series-crime-and-justice-1\">event here</a>. </p>\n<p>This challenge invited teams to consider how open data projects can be constructed that achieve one of the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p>increase community involvement with the criminal justice system</p></li>\n<li><p>create further evidence for what are effective interventions for rehabilitation</p></li>\n<li><p>address the rise in personal crime</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The three finalists are now actively ‘incubating’ the projects and developing their products - the final winner will be announced in Feb 2014. </p>\n<p><strong>Simon Whitehouse</strong> is the Series Lead for Crime and Justice. He can be contacted via <a href=\"si@siwhitehouse.co.uk\" title=\"email\">email</a> or <a href=\"https://twitter.com/siwhitehouse\">Twitter</a>.</p>\n<p>Listen to the three finalists discussing their open data projects;</p>\n<iframe frameborder=\"no\" height=\"133\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/115307696&color=ff6600&auto_play=false&show_artwork=false\" width=\"373.33px\"></iframe>\n<iframe frameborder=\"no\" height=\"133\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/115308066&color=ff6600&auto_play=false&show_artwork=false\" width=\"373.33px\"></iframe>\n<iframe frameborder=\"no\" height=\"133\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/115305648&color=ff6600&auto_play=false&show_artwork=false\" width=\"373.33px float: left;\"></iframe>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>The Crime and Justice Challenge is approaching it's Celebration stage where our three finalists will pitch for the final prize of £40 000. Join us for the evening by signing up to our <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/open-data-challenge-series-crime-and-justice-pitch-and-celebration-event-tickets-10273533415\">Eventbrite</a></p>","media_enquiries_name":"","media_enquiries_email":"","media_enquiries_telephone":"","organizations":[],"author":{"name":"Open Data Institute","slug":"odi","state":"published","web_url":"http://theodi.org/odi","tag_ids":[]}},"related_external_links":[],"related":[],"organizations":[],"author":{"name":"Open Data Institute","slug":"odi","state":"published","web_url":"http://theodi.org/odi","tag_ids":[]}}